title: Album Page, "Elevation of Central Domed Building and Sketches of Beam Profiles", late 19th century
medium: Graphite on very smooth, off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, upper right corner (perpendicular to drawing): 98; bottom right corner (perpendicular to drawing): 86.  Various inscriptions with dimensions and measurements.
dimensions: Sheet: 20.9 x 30.9 cm (8 1/4 x 12 3/16 in.), irregular
description: Horizontal sheet tipped vertically into binding illustrating at center a rough sketch of the elevation of a building with a high dome in the center supported by two smaller arches at the left and right.  To the right of this are two sketches wooden molding profiles, and another smaller sketch of the same elevation at left, but here shown with a low pitched roof above the domes.
